# Tests & eval loops

## Runner

`python run_tests.py <mode>` — modes: `unit`, `tiers`, `settings`, `e2e`, `overnight`, `frontend-lint`, `router-lint`, `all`.

## Markers (pytest.ini)

- `slow` — skip in fast unit runs (`-m "not slow"`).
- `e2e` — requires running API + Playwright.
- `overnight` — long E2E suite for unattended runs.

## E2E

- Helpers: `tests/e2e/helpers/`.
- Config: `tests/e2e/conftest.py`.
- Run: `python run_tests.py e2e`.

## Eval harness (Level 8)

`python scripts/agent/eval_loop.py --json` returns structured pass/fail for agent self-heal loops.

## Writing tests

- Test real behavior, not implementation trivia.
- Prefer existing fixtures in `tests/e2e/conftest.py` for browser tests.
- After fixing a bug, add or extend a test that would have caught it.
